# Repository Layer

## Responsibility

Repositories are the data access layer: CRUD and queries for one aggregate/entity. No business logic; only persistence and retrieval.

## Structure

- Extend `JpaRepository<Entity, Id>` (or `CrudRepository`) for standard CRUD.
- One repository per entity/aggregate root (e.g. `ItemRepository` for `Item`).
- Place in `repository` package; methods return entities, `Optional<Entity>`, or collections (e.g. `List<Item>`).
- Use constructor injection only if you add custom implementation beans; otherwise no explicit `@Autowired` needed on the interface.

## Query Methods

- Prefer **derived query methods** (Spring Data parses method name): `findByStatus`, `findByUserIdOrderByCreatedAtDesc`, `existsByEmail`.
- Use `@Query` for JPQL or native when naming is unclear or for complex conditions; prefer JPQL over native for portability.
- Return `Optional<T>` for single-result methods that may be absent; return `List`/`Page`/`Slice` for multiple results.
- Use `Pageable` for pagination; return `Page<T>` when you need total count, `Slice<T>` when you don’t.

```java
// ✅ GOOD
public interface ItemRepository extends JpaRepository<Item, Long> {
    List<Item> findByStatusOrderByCreatedAtDesc(ItemStatus status, Pageable pageable);
    Optional<Item> findByIdAndUserId(Long id, Long userId);
    boolean existsByName(String name);

    @Query("SELECT i FROM Item i WHERE i.status = :status AND i.user.id = :userId")
    List<Item> findByStatusAndUser(@Param("status") ItemStatus status, @Param("userId") Long userId);
}
```

## Naming

- `findBy...`, `getBy...` (single), `existsBy...`, `countBy...`, `deleteBy...`.
- Use `OrderBy...Asc/Desc` for sort; for dynamic sort use `Pageable` in the method signature.
- Keep method names readable; if they get long or complex, use `@Query` with a clear JPQL statement.

## Don’t

- Put business logic or validation in repositories (belongs in service).
- Expose repository types or entities directly from controllers; map in service to DTOs.
- Use `SELECT *` in JPQL; select only needed fields or the entity when you need the full aggregate.
